    </header>
    <div>
        <section style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
            <h2>What Are FPV Drones?</h2>
            <p>FPV (First Person View) drones provide an immersive flying experience by transmitting live video from an onboard camera to a pair of goggles or a monitor, allowing pilots to see from the drone's perspective.</p>
            <div class="image-placeholder"></div>
        </section>
        
        <section style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
            <h2>Key Components</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Frame:</strong> Sturdy and lightweight structure, often made from carbon fiber.</li>
                <li><strong>Motors:</strong> Brushless motors for efficient and long-lasting performance.</li>
                <li><strong>ESCs:</strong> Electronic Speed Controllers to regulate motor power.</li>
                <li><strong>Flight Controller:</strong> The drone's brain, managing inputs and sensors.</li>
                <li><strong>Camera:</strong> Captures real-time video for the pilot.</li>
                <li><strong>VTX:</strong> Video Transmitter that sends the video feed to goggles or monitors.</li>
                <li><strong>Receiver:</strong> Receives control commands from the pilot's transmitter.</li>
                <li><strong>Batteries:</strong> LiPo batteries providing power to the drone.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="image-placeholder"></div>
        </section>
        
        <section style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
            <h2>FPV System</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Goggles/Monitor:</strong> Devices that receive the live video feed, offering an immersive view.</li>
                <li><strong>Transmitter:</strong> Remote controller used by the pilot to maneuver the drone.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="image-placeholder"></div>
        </section>
        
        <section style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
            <h2>Types of FPV Drones</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Racing Drones:</strong> Built for speed and agility, ideal for competitive racing.</li>
                <li><strong>Freestyle Drones:</strong> Designed for performing acrobatic maneuvers and tricks.</li>
                <li><strong>Cinewhoops:</strong> Small, ducted drones perfect for capturing cinematic footage.</li>
                <li><strong>Long-Range Drones:</strong> Equipped for extended flight distances, ideal for exploration.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="image-placeholder"></div>
        </section>
        
        <section style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
            <h2>Exciting Features</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Low Latency:</strong> Ensures real-time control and immediate response.</li>
                <li><strong>High-Quality Video:</strong> Provides a clear and immersive viewing experience.</li>
                <li><strong>Durability:</strong> Robust design to withstand crashes, especially in racing and freestyle drones.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="image-placeholder"></div>
        </section>
        
        <section style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
            <h2>Applications</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Recreational Flying:</strong> Enjoy the thrill of flying from a unique perspective.</li>
                <li><strong>Racing:</strong> Participate in competitive drone racing events.</li>
                <li><strong>Cinematography:</strong> Capture stunning aerial footage for films and videos.</li>
                <li><strong>Inspection and Surveying:</strong> Ideal for industrial applications, inspecting hard-to-reach areas.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="image-placeholder"></div>
        </section>
        
        <section style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
            <h2>Important Considerations</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Regulations:</strong> Adhere to local laws, including registration and flight rules.</li>
                <li><strong>Skill Level:</strong> FPV flying requires practice and skill development due to its steep learning curve.</li>
                <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Always fly responsibly to avoid accidents and ensure safety.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="image-placeholder"></div>
        </section>
